  <brief_title>The Effect of Preoperative Pain on POCD in Elderly Patients</brief_title>
  <official_title>The Effect of Preoperative Pain on Postoperative Cognitive Dysfunction in Elderly Patients</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>RenJi Hospital</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>RenJi Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to investigate the effects of preoperative pain on POCD in elder
      patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Postoperative cognitive dysfunction (POCD) occurs mainly in aged patients. The mechanism of
      POCD is not clear yet and no effective therapy method .The purpose of this study is to
      investigate the effects of preoperative pain on POCD in elder patients.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
