  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        Elderly patients underwent elective low limb surgery; Chronic pain duration &gt;1months or
        acute pain duration &lt;1months.
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Non-Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Elder than 65 years old

          2. Speak Chinese Mandarin

          3. Those who will undergo major general surgery like low limb surgery

          4. Signed the inform consent

          5. American Society of Anesthesiologists classification I to II

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Existing cerebral disease, or have a history of neurological and psychiatric disease
             including Alzheimer Disease, stroke, epilepsy and psychosis

          2. Existing cognitive impairment as evidenced by Mini-Mental State Examination scores
             below 24

          3. Severe audition or vision disorder

          4. Unwillingness to comply with the protocol or procedures

          5. Cannot communicated with Chinese Mandarin

          6. Serious heart of liver or renal insufficiency patients

          7. Had surgery in the past 30 days
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
